{% comment -%}---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Function: render_datetime

Description: Format and render the datetime based on the given locale and format. 

Usage:  {% include dynamo function="render_datetime" datetime=page.date 
            locale="en-us" date_format="long" time_format="none" -%}

        {% include dynamo function="render_datetime" datetime=page.date 
            date_format="ISO8601" -%}
        The above code renders the current page date in ISO 8601 format - a format 
        independent of the locale. 

Parameters:
    * datetime      (object) - The datetime to format and render.
    * locale        (string) - The locale for formatting and localizing the datetime 
                               rendering. For example, when date format is "short", 
                               January 9, 2009 renders as 1/9/09 for the "en-us" locale, 
                               and 09/01/2009 for the "fr-fr" locale.
    * date_format   (string) - Date format.  It can be one of the following standard
                               date format strings or any custom date formats. If 
                               date_format is "ISO8601", time_format has to be either 
                               "none" or "ISO8601". Default: "none"

      Standard date formats    Description                      Examples for January 9, 2009
      "none"                   Do not render date in the output
      "ISO8601"                ISO 8601 format                  2009-01-09, regardless of the locale
      "default"                Default date format              Jan 9, 2009 (en-us)
                                                                9 janv. 2009 (fr-fr)
      "short"                  Short date format                1/9/09 (en-us)
                                                                09/01/2009 (fr-fr)
      "medium"                 Medium date format               Jan 9, 2009 (en-us)
                                                                9 janv. 2009 (fr-fr)
      "long"                   Long date format                 January 9, 2009 (en-us)
                                                                9 janvier 2009 (fr-fr)
      "full"                   Full date format                 Friday, January 9, 2009 (en-us)
                                                                vendredi 9 janvier 2009 (fr-fr)
    
    * time_format   (string) - Time format.  It can be one of the following standard
                               time format strings or any custom time formats. If 
                               time_format is "ISO8601", date_format has to be either 
                               "none" or "ISO8601". Default: "none"

      Standard time formats    Description                      Examples for 05:07:04 AM
      "none"                   Do not render time in the output
      "ISO8601"                ISO 8601 format                  05:14:28
      "default"                Default time format              5:07:04 AM (en-us)
                                                                05:07:04 (fr-fr)
      "short"                  Short time format                5:07 AM (en-us)
                                                                05:07 (fr-fr)
      "medium"                 Medium time format               5:07:04 AM (en-us)
                                                                05:07:04 (fr-fr)
      "long"                   Long time format                 5:07:04 AM PST (en-us)
                                                                05:07:04 PST (fr-fr)
      "full"                   Full time format                 5:07:04 AM Pacific Standard Time (en-us)
                                                                05:07:04 heure normale du Pacifique nord-américain (fr-fr)
